“What Wesley Wore” written by Samuel Langley-Swain (@story_dad) illustrated by @ryansonderegger and published by @owletpress . Story provided by @littleboxofbooks
.
As the world grapples with the coronavirus pandemic, children’s lives are being turned upside down. 
By donating to Save with Stories, you can support the most vulnerable families in the UK and around the world by helping to provide early learning packs, supermarket vouchers, essential household items and virus protection.
.
If you can, please donate to Save the Children by visiting @savechildrenuk .
Thank you. Together, we can help families get through this.
.
#SaveWithStoriesUK #SaveWithStories

node.text: This week this virus has affected me even more than it has so far, because people I know have now died of #covid19 it reminds us that no one is immune, young or old, ill or healthy, Rich or poor, it doesn’t care where you’re from, or the colour of your skin. We will all feel it’s effect on our lives and our loved ones. We HAVE to do our part people, we HAVE to stay away from others, We HAVE To #stayhome It’s the only way we can make that horrible curve go down instead of up. I want to dedicate this song to all those  tens of thousands we have lost and to the people who gave their lives working on the frontlines to save others. All of You will NEVER be forgotten. Our gratitude is infinite. 🙏🏼 #ThankyouNHS

node.text: I was 22, I was watching the TV in the gym, the screen was on Silent and I thought it was a scene from a movie that was on pause, only when I looked closer did I realised the reality of what I was seeing. My stomach churned so badly, I left and caught the bus home and stayed indoors glued to the television all day, all I could think about was the poor souls who suffered and died and countless thousands who were left to pick up the pieces physically and emotionally. It will never leave me, it will never leave us. #gonebutneverforgotten
